Wick breach rules:
- Each trendline (resistance and support) is allowed a maximum of 1 wick breach.
- If either trendline has 2 or more wick breaches — REJECT.
- If the total number of wick breaches across both trendlines is 3 or more — REJECT.
Patterns that exceed these thresholds are structurally messy and crowd coordination is unreliable.

TE9. TP REACHED?: Price must NOT have already reached, touched, or exceeded the measured move target. If TP has been touched, reached, or exceeded, the trade opportunity is gone. — REJECT.

